  "page_range": "7-8"
}

Child summaries:
[
  {
    "node_id": "0007",
    "title": "2025年6月份在投手游广告主超过 9万，每月新投手游均值接近 8000",
    "page_range": "8-9",
    "summary": "This section answers retrieval queries regarding the scale, growth trajectory, and new advertiser acquisition rates for the global mobile game advertising market in 2025. It provides specific metrics to answer questions on active advertiser volume (monthly average >84,000, June peak >90,000, annual total >400,000), year-over-year growth (21.9%), and new advertiser dynamics (monthly average ~8,000 at 9.4% share; September, October, and December exceed 10%; annual new advertiser share is 23.4%, stable year-over-year). The section includes figures charting monthly 2025 trends and a 2023–2025 three-year comparative trend. All claims and metrics are substantiated by backend scraped data from the ad intelligence platform 广大大, covering the January–December 2025 period."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0008",
    "title": "每月投新素材广告主已经稳超 8成，新素材占比在 11月份突破 60%",
    "page_range": "9",
    "summary": "This section provides statistical data and trend analysis on new advertising creative adoption in the global mobile game market. It is optimized to answer retrieval queries regarding:\n- **Topics & Scope:** Monthly trends in new creative placement and advertiser adoption rates for global mobile games (2024–2025).\n- **Key Claims & Metrics:** 2025 average monthly percentage of advertisers using new creatives exceeds 82% (chart summary: 82.5%), up 14.6% YoY, peaking at 88.2% in Dec 2025. 2025 average monthly new creative share is 58.1% (+5.9 percentage points YoY), surpassing 60% in Nov 2025 and peaking at 63.2% in Dec 2025.\n- **Dates & Timeframes:** Full range Jan 2024–Dec 2025; monthly data points Feb 2024–Dec 2025; specific emphasis on Nov–Dec 2025 milestones and 2025 annual averages.\n- **Entities:** Global mobile game advertisers; 广大大 (data provider/platform).\n- **Figures & Evidence Types:** Time-series line chart (\"2024&2025 每月投新素材和新素材占比趋势\") tracking two metrics monthly. Evidence type: Backend data scraping and statistical aggregation.\n- **Answerable Queries:** What are the YoY growth rates and monthly peaks for new ad creative adoption in 2025? When did new creative share cross 60%? What is the data source, methodology, and timeframe for global mobile game ad creative trends?"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0009",
    "title": "娱乐场品类营销占比显著提升； RPG产品2025年平均投放超 800条创意",
    "page_range": "10-11",
    "summary": "This section provides statistical insights into 2025 global mobile game marketing trends, structured to answer retrieval queries on category performance, ad volume benchmarks, and market share shifts.\n• **Topics & Entities:** Mobile game advertising/marketing, ad creative placement, game genres (RPG, Strategy, Casino/Entertainment, Casual, Puzzle, Simulation, Action, Arcade, Adventure, Card, Board, Text), data provider (广大大).\n• **Dates:** January–December 2025 (with implied year-over-year comparisons to 2024).\n• **Key Claims & Metrics:** RPG products lead in advertising volume with an average of 801 creatives per product annually; Strategy ranks second at 728. The Casino/Entertainment category experienced the most significant growth, with advertiser share reaching 47% (+22.7% YoY) and creative share at 22.3% (+13.9% YoY). Full ranked metrics for advertiser share, creative share, and average annual creatives across 10+ categories are provided.\n• **Tables & Figures:** Two data tables detailing category-wise advertiser share (%) and creative share (%) with corresponding YoY percentage changes. One ranked list/chart displaying the 2025 average annual creative count per game category.\n• **Evidence Types:** Backend scraped statistical data, comparative YoY analysis, ranked categorical distributions.\n• **Retrieval Questions Answered:** Which mobile game categories had the highest ad creative volume in 2025? How did the Casino/Entertainment category’s advertiser and creative shares change year-over-year? What are the exact market share percentages and YoY shifts for each mobile game genre in 2025? What is the data source and reporting timeframe for these mobile game marketing metrics?"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0010",
    "title": "欧洲成今年唯一月均广告主超 4万地区；港澳台月均素材投放 TOP1 ，北美、大洋洲紧随其后",
    "page_range": "11-12",
    "summary": "This section answers retrieval queries regarding 2025 global mobile game advertising competition and regional marketing intensity. \n**Topics:** Regional mobile game ad campaign volume, advertiser counts, and creative material placement intensity.\n**Entities/Regions:** Europe, North America, Southeast Asia, South America, South Asia, Japan & Korea, Middle East, Oceania, China (Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan), Africa.\n**Dates:** Monthly averages covering January 2025 to December 2025.\n**Metrics & Claims:** Europe is the sole region exceeding 40K monthly average advertisers (46.2K), leading North America by over 6K. Southeast Asia and South America both exceed 30K. For ad creatives, China (HK/Macau/TW) ranks first (122/month), followed by North America (119/month), with Oceania and Japan/Korea both exceeding 110/month.\n**Evidence Types & Source:** Backend scraping data compiled and presented by \"广大大\".\n**Tables/Figures:** Features a comparative bar chart visualizing monthly average advertisers and monthly average creatives across the ten listed regions. References subsequent analytical figures on video material duration and image material types.\n**Retrieval Utility:** Answers questions about top-performing regions for mobile game ad competition, 2025 regional benchmarks for advertiser and creative volume, comparative marketing intensity across global markets, and the underlying data source for these metrics."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0011",
    "title": "2025年视频素材占比74.1%，比去年提升14.2%；图片素材中方形图片占比最高为67.2%",
    "page_range": "12-13",
    "summary": "**Topics:** Global mobile game advertising creative trends, video vs. image format distribution, video duration breakdown, image aspect ratio preferences, OS platform allocation by game weight and ad channel.\n**Entities & Dates:** 2025 (coverage: Jan–Dec 2025), 2024, 2023; iOS, Android; Light/Mid/Heavy mobile games; FB channels, X (Twitter); Data provider: 广大大.\n**Claims & Metrics:** \n- Video creatives reached 74.1% in 2025 (+14.2% YoY); image creatives fell to 24.7% (-11.6% YoY).\n- Video duration: <30s accounts for 58% (≤15s: 12.8%, 16-30s: 45.2%); 31-59s: 35.1%; ≥60s: 6.9%.\n- Image aspect ratio: Square dominates at 67.2%, followed by other (19.1%), vertical (11.5%), horizontal (2.2%).\n- OS by game weight: Light games heavily favor Android (81.0%); mid and heavy games show ~35% iOS share (35.3% and 35.6%).\n- OS by channel: X (Twitter) has the highest iOS advertiser share at 46.6%; FB channels average ~21% iOS.\n**Evidence Types:** Quantitative industry statistics, year-over-year comparative data, categorical percentage breakdowns, chart-derived metrics.\n**Target Retrieval Questions:** What is the 2025 distribution of video vs. image ad creatives for global mobile games? How have creative format shares changed YoY? What are the most common video durations and image aspect ratios? How does OS platform preference vary by game weight (light vs. mid/heavy)? Which ad channels have the highest iOS advertiser share? What is the data source and timeframe for these metrics?"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0012",
    "title": "2025年Android端广告主占比接近80%，中重度产品iOS端广告主占比在35%左右",
    "page_range": "13-14",
    "summary": "**Topics:** Mobile game advertising market share by operating system (iOS vs. Android), ad creative/material distribution by game genre (light, medium, heavy), and platform-specific creative allocation across major ad networks.\n**Entities:** Android, iOS, 广大大 (ad intelligence data provider), Facebook (FB) ad channels, UnityAds, mobile game advertisers/publishers.\n**Dates:** January 2025 – December 2025.\n**Key Metrics & Claims:**\n- Overall mobile game advertiser share: Android 79.6%, iOS 20.4%.\n- Genre-based iOS material share: Light 13.0%, Medium 26.1%, Heavy 32.6% (Android shares are 87.0%, 73.9%, and 67.4% respectively).\n- Claim: Heavier game gameplay correlates with a higher proportion of iOS ad creatives.\n- Channel-specific shares: FB channels iOS creative share ~28%; UnityAds Android material share peaks at 93.5%. Additional iOS/Android material share percentages are provided for other unnamed popular ad channels.\n**Evidence & Data Types:** Quantitative market statistics, platform/channel performance breakdowns, and comparative charts/tables (pages 13–14) sourced from backend ad tracking data.\n**Retrieval Questions Answered:** \n- What is the iOS vs. Android advertiser share for global mobile games in 2025?\n- How does mobile game genre (light/medium/heavy) impact iOS vs. Android ad creative distribution?\n- Which ad networks show the highest Android or iOS material shares in 2025?\n- What is the data source, timeframe, and page location for 2025 mobile game ad platform analysis?"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0013",
    "title": "游戏玩法越重度则iOS端素材创意占比越高，主流渠道Android素材占比大部分在70%以上",
    "page_range": "14-15",
    "summary": "This section addresses 2025 global mobile game advertising creative distribution by operating system. It can answer retrieval queries regarding:\n- **Topics & Claims:** The positive correlation between heavier game gameplay and increased iOS creative asset share; the observation that mainstream advertising channels typically allocate over 70% of creatives to Android.\n- **Metrics & Figures:** Exact global asset proportions (iOS: 22.7%, Android: 77.3%), visualized in a chart on page 14.\n- **Entities & Scope:** Global mobile games, iOS, Android, and mainstream ad channels.\n- **Dates:** Full-year coverage from January to December 2025.\n- **Evidence & Source:** Industry data scraped, processed, and published by the analytics platform 广大大.\nIdeal for queries on mobile ad creative allocation trends, platform-specific marketing strategies, gameplay-driven ad planning, and 2025 gaming industry advertising metrics."
  }
]
